Title: Abelian and Non-Abelian Induced Parity Breaking Terms at Finite

TemperatureAuthors: C.D.Fosco (1), G.L.Rossini (2,3) and F.A.Schaposnik (3) ((1) Centro

Atomico Bariloche, Argentina (2) Massachusetts Institute of Technology, (3)Universidad Nacional de La Plata, Argentina)Comments: 13 pages, RevTeX, no figures

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D56 (1997) 6547-6555

We compute the exact canonically induced parity breaking part of theeffective action for 2+1 massive fermions in particular Abelian and non Abeliangauge field backgrounds. The method of computation resorts to the chiralanomaly of the dimensionally reduced theory.